This package's installation was, by far, the most interesting. The configuration/compilation went smoothly, and most of the compilation was okay, until the very end. A specific script (it was head_bison.py or make_bison.py or something), which would generate a file, that is required for compiling this package, but, rather than use said file, the script deletes it. I had to go online, look up the issue, do some digging, and find a fix. I found a user, who had reported the issue, and provided a patch. I had to figure out how to adapt said patch, so it would work with my build, and, after several failures, I got it working. This way very fun, and very satisfiying.
